<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-09-20T23:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-09-20T23:00:00-05:00" n="730" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d730">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/9–2146: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-09-21T13:00:00+09:00">September 21,
                                1946—1 p.m.</date>
                            <lb/> [Received September 25—1:42 p.m.]</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>1518. General Marshall has approved for transmission following message from
                        him to Acting Secretary of State (1538): <quote rend="blockquote">
                            <p>“Reference your 518<note n="50" xml:id="d730fn50">Telegram of July
                                    26, <ref target="#pg_996">p. 996</ref>.</note> and my 1235<note n="51" xml:id="d730fn51">Telegram of July 31, <ref target="#pg_996">p. 996</ref>.</note> of July, I would not
                                object to ‘working level’ discussion regarding material or technical
                                assistance for the reconstruction or repair of rail communications
                                because they are urgently needed as the basis for reconstituting a
                                reasonable national economy. Otherwise, I concur in Department’s
                                views outlined in Urtel 758, September 16, 8 p.m.”</p>
                        </quote>
                    </p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>